latestPosts.caption:
A procession that winds through the streets of Mysore, accompanied by intricately decorated elephants and a cavalcade of dancers and musicians. Performers such as Dollu Kunita, Garudi Gombe, and Veeragase dance narrate tales from Hindu epics and regional folklore, enriching the procession’s narrative.

This harmonious blend of regal heritage and communal participation transforms Mysore into a living canvas, where every element—from the towering elephants to the rhythmic dances—tells a story of enduring legacy and collective pride.
